description.value: Gypsum alabaster (calcium sulphate) alabastron with pointed end; terminating in a female figure.  The lip of the vase and nose of the woman are broken away. The upper part of the alabastron is terminating in the bust of a woman on top of whose head the vase's lip was placed. The figure is wearing a long-sleeved garment and a thin veil, falling over the hair and shoulders towards the front; the ears are not covered and the veil might as well be a wig-like hairstyle. She is wearing a necklace which is falling down to her breasts which she clasps with her right hand; alternatively it has been suggested that she is holding another object thus covering the necklace. The left arm is hanging at the side, the fingers are clenched with the thumb projecting. The face is rather rounded with a pointed chin. The slim oblique eyes are fairly long, the lower lid is more or less straight, the upper plastically rendered. The mouth is smiling broadly with full lips; the nose is short with a broadening tip. The back is left round.
